,Recommended,302490,26687546,"Posted: 19 November, 2016",all,tvleavitt,"TL;DR: Simple, sweet way to while away a few hours without stress. Easy on the eyes and ears. Unquestionably worth sale price.Full review: Cute. Simple. Amusing. Very high quality production values: zero bugs, high quality art (if a bit cliched, the iron jawed male hero and impossibly thin female characters are a bit much) varying from merely competent to lush and lovely. The music is nothing spectacular, but fits the scenery and mood properly and isn't intrusive or boring. I happily let it play on through the whole game without becoming annoyed.I played the game through in a single evening on the lower difficulty ""Adventure Mode"" setting (several of the eight hours Steam recorded were where I walked away from the game for dinner and chatter with roommates), and found it exactly what I was looking for in terms of difficultly and engagement for a stress free evening. Every two or three levels, I screwed up the initial run through enough to restart, either part way through, or after finishing and being awarded a ""Silver"" star. Obtaining the desired ""Gold"" star required paying enough attention to what I was doing that I remained throughly immersed. This is definitely a ""casual"" game (at least in ""Adventure"" mode), suitable for youngun's or folks looking for to while away a few relaxed hours. The story, which is, yes, cheesy as heck, unfolds neatly as you go along, each level taking no more than a few minutes and leading neatly into the  next and the one after that.If you're ""hardcore"" or in the mood for a ""serious"" challenge leading to the occassional frustrated outburst, this isn't the game for you. I beat every level at the ""Gold"" star rank on my first or second try (although there were a couple of close calls with the latter). While there's probably zero replayablity--I, personally, have no impulse to go through it again on ""Heroic Mode"" (the higher level of difficulty)--that's not a big deal at the sale price of under $2 that I paid for it."
